Dave Rubin explains that disagreement with Trump isn’t the problem — bad faith is.

Good-faith criticism can sharpen decisions and strengthen leadership. Iron sharpens Iron. But that only works when it’s done honestly— not in bad faith like Tucker Carlson.

@RubinReport: "You 100% can have principled arguments against Trump or anybody else, but that's not what Tucker's been doing—he's been lying..."

